snippet: Hundreds of young Muslim Brotherhood members blocked a protest from reaching Parliament while its lawmakers inside dominated the selection of committee leaders.
abstract: Hundreds of young Muslim Brotherhood members block a protest from reaching the Egyptian Parliament, where party's lawmakers dominated the selection of committee leaders; more than 70 people are injured in clash; confrontation illustrates the Brotherhood's transition from an outlawed Islamist group to the country's central power bloc, holding half the seats in the newly elected Parliament.

byline.contributor: Liam Stack and Mayy El Sheikh contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Hundreds of young Muslim Brotherhood members blocked a protest from reaching Parliament while its lawmakers inside dominated the selection of committee leaders.
